HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 801
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Sarah Elizabeth
Bowden-Threet of Lawrenceburg.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Sarah Elizabeth Bowden-Threet of Lawrenceburg; and
WHEREAS, Sarah Elizabeth Bowden-Threet was an exemplary public servant and
consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow
citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born on February 24, 1933, in Lawrenceburg, Ms. Bowden-Threet was the
daughter of John Morgan and Pearl Pitts; and
WHEREAS, greatly admired by her community and colleagues, Sarah Bowden-Threet
enjoyed a distinguished career in banking and retired as vice president of Lawrence County
Bank; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Bowden-Threet earned many achievements in her professional career,
including the Lawrence County Business and Professional Women's AP Diamond Award; and
WHEREAS, Sarah Bowden-Threet was an active member of the Mars Hill United
Methodist Church, where she served faithfully for many years; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Bowden-Threet was deeply devoted to her family, and she always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Sarah Bowden-Threet is survived by her daughter, Beth Bowden-Jones;
grandson, Ben (Sarah) Luna; stepchildren, Sherry Threet Montgomery, Lisa Threet (Jim)
Snyder, and Philip (Joy) Threet; step-grandchildren, Allie (Ryan) Philpot, Laura (Wesley) Long,
Erin (Chance) Pearcy, Kayla (TJ) Whitehead, Kelli (Matt) Fowler, Katie (Mat) Naughton, Joshua
(Samantha) Montgomery, and Jeremy (Holly) Montgomery; nine step-great-grandchildren; and
several nieces, nephews, and cousins; and
HJR0801
011441
- 1 -

WHEREAS, in addition to her parents, Ms. Bowden-Threet was preceded in death by
her sisters, Nova Jewel Perry and Jane Morgan Pitts; first husband, W.O. Bowden, Jr.; second
husband, J.W. Threet; and son-in-law, Terry Jones; and
WHEREAS, Sarah Bowden-Threet leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and
probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all
her chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Sarah Elizabeth Bowden-Threet, reflecting fondly
upon her impeccable character and her stalwart commitment to living the examined life with
courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Ms. Bowden-Threet.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
